These pains you feel are messengers. Listen to them.‚Äù Rumi‚†Ä
‚†Ä
I talk a lot about symptoms and signs. And the importance of finding their underlying root cause and addressing this. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Recently though I have been working with clients with no obvious symptoms. And I thought it was equally important to also share this. ‚†Ä

Their focus is on optimising their health and wellbeing, and prevention. Which is fantastic and something I‚Äôm so passionate about. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
But what I often find with these clients, using functional lab testing, is they do have some functional level deficiencies or imbalances. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This often comes as a shock, especially for those that live a healthy lifestyle. But picking it up now is a lot easier and less painful than the alternative. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Again it is so important to ask why and get to the root cause.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Yes, you may be asymptomatic, but there is always a reason for an imbalance in your body. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Often we get so busy working or taking care of everyone else that we stop listening to our own body. And these silent signs become our new normal. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
It‚Äôs not until clients see their lab results do they realise that these signs have been there for a while. And they see how it is impacting their health. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Chronic conditions don‚Äôt just happen they develop slowly over many years. It is the accumulation of toxins and stress over time that wears your body down. And makes it more susceptible to deficiencies, and ultimately disease.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Unfortunately today it‚Äôs often not until someone gets sick that their health becomes their number one priority. And this is something I would love to change. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
I would love to see functional lab testing become mainstream as it can do so much for preventative and optimised health. Helping us deal with the ever growing number of toxins and stressors in our lives. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
